commit.message:
DEVPROD-2553: migrate to garasign for signing (#634)

This commit removes our use of the legacy Notary service in favor of
Garasign for both PGP signing as well as Authenticode signing. MacOS
artifacts are still signed with MacOS Notary. Our signing code has been
moved to a single script that branches based on the operating system we
are signing for. Notably, this commit has removed signing for our RPMs.
This was done because we were signing those RPMs with a now-EOL server
key, which leads me to believe that no one was actually verifying these
signatures in practice. Users would have had to magically know which key
to use, and we have not be publicizing this information anywhere. If
removal of RPM signing breaks someone's workflow, it can be added back
in, though users can get signed RPMs directly from repo.mongodb.{com|org}
instead.

committer GitHub <noreply@github.com> 1709663994 -0500

DEVPROD-2553: migrate to garasign for signing (#634)

This commit removes our use of the legacy Notary service in favor of
Garasign for both PGP signing as well as Authenticode signing. MacOS
artifacts are still signed with MacOS Notary. Our signing code has been
moved to a single script that branches based on the operating system we
are signing for. Notably, this commit has removed signing for our RPMs.
This was done because we were signing those RPMs with a now-EOL server
key, which leads me to believe that no one was actually verifying these
signatures in practice. Users would have had to magically know which key
to use, and we have not be publicizing this information anywhere. If
removal of RPM signing breaks someone's workflow, it can be added back
in, though users can get signed RPMs directly from repo.mongodb.{com|org}
instead.

commit.message:
TOOLS-3411 Fix issue where sort order of views was not always preserved on dump (#618)

Fixes an issue where mongodump did not always preserve the order of options for a view or collection. This could result in different sort orders than expected on views. It is easily fixed by moving from the unordered bson.M type to the ordered bson.D type for collection options. Index options are still a bson.M, but the keys are bson.D so they are not affected by this issue.

commit.message:
TOOLS-3370 TOOLS-3371 Add 7.0 tests and rework test suites (#607)

- Remove tests for all variants except for:
    - Windows
    - RHEL 8
    - RHEL 6 w/o SASL/Kerberos (Splunk build)
- Add tests for 7.0.
- Replace the python script for downloading server and shell versions with Go code.
- Download the correct `jstestshell` for each version.
- Upgrade to Go 1.20.
- Run `gofmt` with 1.20 which changes indentation on several comment blocks.
- Make the `h` field `omitempty` when marshaling oplog entries in mongodump. This is because the `h` field was removed in 7.1 since it was unused for many versions. Also proactively strip `h` fields when running `applyOps` for 7.0+.
